{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Psa|14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","chapter":14,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v11","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:14:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":14,"verse":1,"text":"The fool says in his heart, “There’s no God.” They are corrupt; they do vile deeds. There is no one who does good.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:14:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":14,"verse":2,"text":"The Lord looks down from heaven on the human race to see if there is one who is wise, one who seeks God.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:14:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":14,"verse":3,"text":"All have turned away; all alike have become corrupt. There is no one who does good, not even one.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:14:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":14,"verse":4,"text":"Will evildoers never understand? They consume my people as they consume bread; they do not call on the Lord.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:14:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":14,"verse":5,"text":"Then they will be filled with dread, for God is with those who are righteous.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:14:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":14,"verse":6,"text":"You sinners frustrate the plans of the oppressed, but the Lord is his refuge.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:14:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":14,"verse":7,"text":"Oh, that Israel’s deliverance would come from Zion! When the Lo